The shrine enshrines the war dead from Yamaguchi Prefecture who perished in national crises since the {{ill|Meiji Restoration|ja|明治維新|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Restoration|qq=}}. This includes notable figures such as {{ill|Yoshida Shoin|ja|吉田松陰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Shoin|qq=}}, {{ill|Kusaka Genzui|ja|久坂玄瑞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kusaka Genzui|qq=}}, {{ill|Kijima Matabei|ja|来島又兵衛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kijima Matabei|qq=}}, {{ill|Omura Masujiro|ja|大村益次郎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omura Masujiro|qq=}}, {{ill|Takasugi Shinsaku|ja|高杉晋作|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takasugi Shinsaku|qq=}}, and {{ill|Gessho|ja|月性|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gessho|qq=}}.

After {{ill|World War II|ja|第二次世界大戦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/World War II|qq=}}, Self-Defense Force personnel from Yamaguchi Prefecture who died in the line of duty have also been enshrined.

== History ==
In 1903 (Meiji 36), the {{ill|Bocho Yasukenkai|ja|防長靖献会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bocho Yasukenkai|qq=}} was established in Yamaguchi Prefecture, and memorial services were held at the Sakura Batake parade ground (now the training ground for the {{ill|Japan Ground Self-Defense Force|ja|陸上自衛隊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan Ground Self-Defense Force|qq=}} {{ill|Yamaguchi Garrison|ja|山口駐屯地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Garrison|qq=}}) adjacent to the current location.

In 1939 (Showa 14), it was decided to establish a Gokoku Shrine in Yamaguchi Prefecture. The shrine was completed at its current location in August 1941 (Showa 16). It was designated as an Interior Minister-designated Gokoku Shrine, and on November 26 of the same year, 7159 spirits from Yamaguchi Prefecture who were enshrined at {{ill|Yasukuni Shrine|ja|靖国神社|1=Yasukuni Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasukuni Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasukuni Shrine|qq=}} were transferred here. The enshrinement ceremony was held on November 27.

== location Information ==
; location
: Yamaguchi Prefecture, Yamaguchi City, Hirano 2-2-1
; Transportation
: Railway
: {{ill|Yamaguchi Station (Yamaguchi Prefecture)|ja|山口駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Station (Yamaguchi Prefecture)|qq=}} ({{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/West Japan Railway Company|qq=}} (JR West) {{ill|Yamaguchi Line|ja|山口線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Line|qq=}}) - 10 minutes by car

