'''Yamaguchi Prefecture Gokoku Shrine'''（山口縣護國神社{{ill|Yamaguchi Gokoku Shrine|lt=Yamaguchi Gokoku Shrine|lt=Yamaguchi Prefecture Gokoku Shrine|ja|山口縣護國神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Prefecture Gokoku Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=山口県護国神社}}）is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] ([[:en:Gokoku shrines|Gokoku Shrine]]) located in [[:en:Yamaguchi (city)|Yamaguchi City]], [[:en:Yamaguchi Prefecture|Yamaguchi Prefecture]].

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the war dead from Yamaguchi Prefecture who perished in national crises since the [[:en:Meiji Restoration|Meiji Restoration]]. This includes notable figures such as [[:en:Yoshida Shōin|Yoshida Shoin]], [[:en:Kusaka Genzui|Kusaka Genzui]], [[:en:Kijima Matabē|Kijima Matabei]], [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Omura Masujiro]], [[:en:Takasugi Shinsaku|Takasugi Shinsaku]], and {{ill|Gessho|ja|月性|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gessho|qq=|1=Gesshō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6605593}}.

After [[:en:World War II|World War II]], Self-Defense Force personnel from Yamaguchi Prefecture who died in the line of duty have also been enshrined.

== History ==
In 1903 (Meiji 36), the {{ill|Bocho Yasukenkai|ja|防長靖献会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bocho Yasukenkai|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} was established in Yamaguchi Prefecture, and memorial services were held at the Sakura Batake parade ground (now the training ground for the [[:en:Japan Ground Self-Defense Force|Japan Ground Self-Defense Force]] {{ill|Yamaguchi Garrison|ja|山口駐屯地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaguchi Garrison|qq=|1=Camp Yamaguchi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11467540}}) adjacent to the current location.

In 1939 (Showa 14), it was decided to establish a Gokoku Shrine in Yamaguchi Prefecture. The shrine was completed at its current location in August 1941 (Showa 16). It was designated as an Interior Minister-designated Gokoku Shrine, and on November 26 of the same year, 7159 spirits from Yamaguchi Prefecture who were enshrined at [[:en:Yasukuni Shrine|Yasukuni Shrine]] were transferred here. The enshrinement ceremony was held on November 27.

